5:
A mission— Er, I mean, a request for
my services?
7:
Oh, won't you say yes? All you have
to do is act as a bodyguard. You're
maid—sorry—MADE for this kind of
job!
10:
Piece of cake. Definitely easier than
baking a cake, that's for sure.
12:
You'll get the hang of that too, with
enough practice!
13:
Now, to business. The man you'll be
guarding will be hosting a ball in a
few days' time.
17:
You'll be attending the ball not as a
maid, but as his guest.
22:
Exactly! Which means you'll need to
look the part. Don't you worry—we'll
find the perfect ball gown for you!
27:
I suddenly remembered an urgent
errand that will demand my full
attention until... When is the ball over?
31:
Huh, so that's why you're all dressed
up like that.
34:
There were so many dresses. Even
now, when I close my eyes, all I can
see is silk, ruffles, and lace...
38:
You look just like a storybook
princess.
42:
I appreciate the sentiment, Stella.
Though I don't know how many
princesses walk around with
concealed firearms.
44:
At any rate, thanks for agreeing to
accompany me. I feel better with
some friendly faces at the ball.
48:
We'll be working behind the scenes.
Just call on us if you need a hand!
50:
Well, I guess we should go and greet
our host!
55:
Hello, is anybody home? We've
come from the Maids' Parlor!
60:
Now that you're here, I'll brief you on
the mission parameters. Leave your
bags at the entryway—they'll be
taken to your rooms shortly.
61:
...Well, what are you waiting for?
Enter. I hope you don't mind, but tea
will be served while we talk tactics.
64:
Is it just me, or does he sound like
the old Marianne?
67:
I'm starting to understand why I was
chosen for this job...
72:
You'll have to pardon me. I've only
recently come into my fortune, so I
haven't had time to polish any
"social graces" or what have you. I
am the lord of this manor. It's a
pleasure.
79:
Psst, Marianne? We're in a posh
manor, not the military. Remember?
83:
Ahem. Many pardons, Milord. If I
recall, you requested my presence
as your guest and bodyguard.
85:
Precisely. Apparently, it's a faux pas
for the host to attend these events
alone. It would attract the wrong
kind of attention.
86:
To be frank, I don't understand these
fussy rituals, but I need to keep up
appearances if I want my business
to succeed. Whatever gets the job
done, I suppose.
88:
So that's why you made a request to
the Maids' Parlor.
90:
Yes. I couldn't ask for just anyone,
however, considering the potential
danger.
92:
And that's where Marianne comes
in. She's more than capable of
taking care of herself and acting as
your security detail, right?
94:
It was the most logical course of
action.
96:
G-gotcha... Well, I guess if anyone
can handle a job like this, it's
Marianne.
98:
I've no doubt you'll fulfill your duty,
Miss Marianne. Well, what say you?
101:
Understood. Should things get
messy, I'm no stranger to disposing
of the trash. On that front, you've no
need to worry.
102:
However, you'll need more than just
a bodyguard. You're hosting this ball
to raise your profile, aren't you?
You'll need it be a smashing success.
105:
The Maids' Parlor offers full-service
support: everything from catering to
staffing to cleanup. Assuming, of
course, that it's within your budget.
107:
Think of it as hiring a group of
top-tier mercenaries—they'll provide
you with exactly what you need, for
the right price.
113:
The catering and the staff for the
ball are all set. Leave everything to
us!
115:
Thank you. ...Sorry for heaping all
this on you out of the blue. But I am
grateful—I couldn't have handled all
this on my own.
118:
Oh, there's no need to be modest!
With an event this big, you need all
hands on deck. Besides, everyone's
pockets are a little jinglier, if you
know what I mean. And it's all thanks
to you!
120:
...Amazing. To think, you've done all
this in such a short amount of time.
123:
The Maids' Parlor has a full
complement of experts in various
fields. It was no problem at all.
125:
You don't say. Well, I'm glad to have
you on my side.
127: Not at all, sir. I mean, Milord.
129:
That being said, the success of this
mission depends on your hard work.
133:
How is your dancing? If you'd like, I
can take you through the steps.
139:
...I'll do whatever it takes. Lead the
way.
